-- Germany May Agree on Transaction Tax by March, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-01-18T07:10:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/germany-may-agree-on-transaction-tax-by-march-handelsblatt-says.html
The German coalition government may
have an agreement on a financial transaction tax by March,
 Handelsblatt  said, citing  Peter Altmaier , the chief whip for
 Chancellor Angela Merkel ’s Christian Democrats.  There are “signals” that Merkel’s Free Democratic
coalition partner would negotiate over the introduction of the
tax, the German newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
